	"keywords": "Terraform, Infrastructure As Code, DevOps, Workflow",
	"description": "A workflow, or a pattern of the work, gives you a standardized way to do\nsomething. \n\nIt is extremely helpful in a team, and can benefit you even if you work\nindividually. A good workflow enables you to streamline a process, organize it,\nand make it less error-prone.\n\nThis article summaries several approaches when working with Terraform, both\nindividually and in a team. I tried to gather the most common ones, but you\nmight also want to develop your own.\n\nThe common requirement for all of them is",
	"headline": "Terraform Workflow: How to Work Individually and in a Team",
